description: Twelve years after a man was sentenced to life imprisonment for allegedly burning his wife to death in Tamil Nadu, the apex court has acquitted him. The court noted inconsistencies in the dying declarations of the deceased and the absence of substantial evidence against the accused. The bench emphasized the need for corroborative evidence when dying declarations are contradictory.
title: 12 years after life term, SC acquits Tamil Nadu man of burning wife to death

description: Assam is in talks with Isro to launch a Rs 450-500 crore geostationary satellite to monitor illegal infiltration, provide flood warnings, and support farmers with weather data. CM Himanta Biswa Sarma announced the plan after allocating funds in the 2025-26 budget. The proposal includes other tech initiatives such as an AI-powered anti-deepfake lab and a bamboo smart city.
title: Assam in talks with Isro, may be first state to have own satellite

description: BJP MLA Tapasi Mondal switched to TMC, citing her dissatisfaction with BJP's divisive politics and lack of central leadership responses. This move reduces BJP's effective strength in the Bengal assembly from 77 to 65 seats. Mondal emphasized her inability to work effectively as a CPM MLA in 2016 and now supports Mamata Banerjee's development politics.
title: BJP MLA Tapasi Mondal joins TMC
Court rejects Rashid’s plea for parole to attend House

description: An Indian-origin international drug lord, Shawn Bhinder, connected to a major US drug seizure, was apprehended in Ludhiana after fleeing FBI capture. Bhinder, who was involved in smuggling cocaine from Colombia, had been operating under the pretense of a legitimate transport business in Canada since 2014.
title: Drug trafficker wanted by FBI held in Punjab
ED searches in Rajasthan, Noida, Mumbai

description: Tech billionaire and DOGE head Elon Musk revealed that X faced a significant cyberattack originating from the Ukraine area, causing widespread service disruptions. Thousands of users reported issues, with outages peaking early Monday morning and continuing intermittently throughout the day. The attack suggests involvement from a large, coordinated group or a country.
title: Elon Musk claims 'cyberattack' on X originated from 'Ukraine area'

description: The Allahabad High Court has directed the ASI to provide a detailed reply regarding the necessity of whitewashing, extra lighting, and decorative lights outside the Jama Masjid in Sambhal, Uttar Pradesh. The directive follows a petition by the mosque management and highlights the need for further examination by ASI experts.
title: File report on need for Sambhal masjid whitewash: HC to ASI

description: Foreigners from the US and UK are crossing into Myanmar via Mizoram to provide arms training to local insurgents, according to Mizoram's chief minister. The Center has heightened surveillance in border areas following involvement from China and the US in the Myanmar conflict. The re-imposition of the protected area regime in Mizoram aims to monitor foreigner movements more closely.
title: Foreigners entering Myanmar via Mizoram to train rebels: CM

description: A C-17 Indian military plane evacuated 283 Indians who were trapped at the Thai-Myanmar border after scam call centers in Myawaddy, Myanmar. Another 240 are expected to be repatriated soon. These Indian nationals were misled with fake job offers and held in poor conditions while being forced into online scams. Authorities coordinated the rescue operation.
title: India airlifts 283 citizens rescued from Myanmar

description: In Ara district, six criminals posing as customers looted jewellery worth Rs 25 crore from a showroom. Bihar Police arrested two suspects following a high-speed chase and gunfight, recovering jewellery worth Rs 15 crore. Items recovered from the suspects include two bags of the loot, two pistols, and a bike.
title: Jewellery worth Rs 25 crore robbed from showroom

description: Rajasthan CM Bhajan Lal Sharma caused a political stir by referring to PM Narendra Modi as his favourite actor. Congress used this to criticize Modi, claiming the PM is more of an actor than a leader. BJP defended Modi, asserting the question was about a 'hero.' The dispute gained significant attention on social media.
title: Modi ‘my favourite actor’, says Rajasthan CM, gives Congress anti-PM ammo

description: The government informed Parliament that the literacy rate among Muslims has risen to 79.5% in 2023-24, although it remains below the 80.9% rate for all religious groups. Additionally, the participation of Muslim women in the labour force has notably increased from 15% in 2021-22 to 21.4% in 2023-24, despite a dip in 2022-23.
title: Muslim literacy, participation of women in workforce up: Rijiju

description: Justice B R Gavai emphasized the integral role of personal data protection in the digital age as part of the right to privacy and life. Addressing challenges like misinformation, online harassment, and emerging technologies, he highlighted the need for judiciaries in developing countries to define limits on digital rights and governmental regulation.
title: Protection of personal data part of right to privacy: Gavai

description: A parliamentary committee has raised concerns over the meagre Rs 575 crore allocation in the 2025-26 Budget for census and NPR updation and recommended completing the census promptly. The panel also suggested establishing a separate central police force to address the surge in cybercrimes and urged the home ministry to seek increased funding for central police forces.
title: Set up NIA-like agency to fight cybercrime, says Parliament panel
Survivor returns to Israel; Hampi sees exodus

description: The state's first Budget after Mahayuti govt's win reveals a record-high debt of Rs 9.3 lakh crore and a revenue deficit of Rs 45,891 crore for 2025-26. No new major schemes are introduced, focusing instead on existing ones. Local body poll budget allocations have increased, and new taxes are proposed to generate Rs 1,125 crore revenue.
title: As debt mounts, Maharashtra cuts Ladki funds, stalls loan waiver

description: ED conducted searches at former Chhattisgarh CM Bhupesh Baghel's premises in connection with a Rs 2,161 crore liquor scam and money laundering involving his son Chaitanya. Assets worth Rs 205 crore have been attached. The searches led to the discovery of significant cash and documents implicating various individuals.
title: ED searches Baghel, son’s premises in Chhattisgarh booze scam

description: In the Jammu and Kashmir Assembly, CM Omar Abdullah condemned the killing of three civilians in Kathua district, calling for a thorough probe. Questions arose over why only BJP politicians were allowed to meet the victims' families while others were not. A security review meeting was held, emphasizing the need for synergy among agencies to ensure peace.
title: Billawar killings: Omar, Iltija ask why only BJP netas meeting victims' kin

description: Videos of models walking the runway in Gulmarg during Ramadan sparked outrage, led by J&K chief cleric Mirwaiz Umar Farooq, who deemed it 'obscene.' Designer duo Shivan & Narresh apologized, citing a desire to respect local traditions. The J&K assembly and political figures condemned the show, while Panun Kashmir opposed the backlash as religious supremacy.
title: Catwalk on snow during Ramadan raises J&K's hackles, CM Omar disowns event

description: In Pakistan's Baluchistan province, three Sindhi barbers were killed by unidentified gunmen in a targeted attack in Panjgur district. The gunmen, who fled on a motorbike, are suspected to be Baluch separatist militants. This incident is part of a series of targeted killings of non-Baluch residents, often accused of espionage for the Pakistani military.
title: Three Sindhi barbers killed in Balochistan

description: LaMelo Ball is set to play against the Miami Heat on March 10, providing a boost for the struggling Charlotte Hornets. Key players like Brandon Miller and Tre Mann are still out, but Miles Bridges has been performing well. Miami, also dealing with injuries, will rely on Bam Adebayo and Tyler Herro as they aim for victory.
title: Will LaMelo Ball play tonight against the Miami Heat?
70% of prisoners in India are undertrials, can’t afford bail: Parliamentary panel calls for urgent reforms
Air India Express expands fleet to 100 planes

description: Elon Musk has confirmed that Twitter (now known as X) is facing a global outage due to a significant cyberattack. He suggested that a large, coordinated group or a country might be involved. Musk acknowledged the continuous attacks, emphasizing the extensive resources used in this particular incident.
title: Elon Musk says, Twitter hit by cyberattack: We are attacked everyday, but ...
10 facts about Vanuatu, the Pacific Island nation that cancelled Lalit Modi’s passport

description: The entertainment world is buzzing with major updates! From Yuzvendra Chahal’s outing with RJ Mahvash amid his divorce from Dhanashree Verma to Govinda revealing he was thrown out of BR Chopra’s office, and Akshay Kumar selling his Mumbai apartment—here are the top five entertainment stories of the day that have everyone talking!
title: Chahal's outing, Govinda thrown out of office: Top 5 entertainment news

description: The deceased man has been identified as Varadaraj, a textile merchant in Perugopanapalli village near Mathur.
title: Man’s body brought to marriage hall to ‘solemnise’ wedding of son in TN
US expands warning of deportation to green card holders after activist's arrest

description: Two youths from Haryana and Punjab have been kidnapped in Guatemala, prompting their families to seek urgent help from the Indian government. Yuvraj Singh, one of the victims, was traveling to the US through an agent but was held hostage, with kidnappers demanding a $20,000 ransom. A distressing video shows the youths being tortured. Authorities have escalated the matter, and an investigation is underway to take action against those responsible.
title: 2 Indians 'kidnapped' in Guatemala, parents seek govt's help

description: Holi, the festival of colours, brings joy, togetherness, and fun activities like splashing water, eating Gujiyas, and sending wishes to loved ones. Celebrated on March 14 in 2025, Holi involves creating unforgettable memories and spreading happiness through vibrant festivities.
title: Heartwarming Happy Holi 2025 wishes and messages to write on cards
Stone hits ED vehicle leaving Bhupesh Baghel's home after raid: Officials
Watch: Oil tanker collides with ship off UK Coast, causing 'massive fireball'

description: Former Indian cricketer Yograj Singh praised Rohit Sharma for his decision to continue playing ODIs after a stellar performance in the Champions Trophy final. He emphasized that both Rohit and Virat Kohli should consider retirement only after the 2027 ODI World Cup. Rohit's crucial 76-run knock against New Zealand was key to India's victory.
title: Yograj suggests when Rohit, Kohli should retire from ODIs
After citizenship blow, Lalit Modi calls Vanuatu 'truly heavenly'

description: Nearly 300 Indians returned home via Thailand after being rescued from scam centers in Myanmar. A crackdown, mainly targeting Chinese-run fraud hubs, has led to the release of 7,000 workers. India deployed a C-17 aircraft for repatriation, with more to follow. These scam centers exploit foreign workers for online fraud. While India welcomed its citizens, China treated its repatriated nationals as criminal suspects.
title: C-17 plane brings back nearly 300 Indians rescued from Myanmar scam centres

description: Mark Carney, set to become Canada's next Prime Minister, aims to strengthen trade relations with India. Winning 85.9% of the Liberal Party vote, Carney emphasizes diversifying trade ties and values-based commercial relationships. His expertise in India's economy through Brookfield Asset Management bodes well for enhancing Canada-India economic and strategic connections.
title: 'Opportunities to rebuild ...': What new Canada PM Mark Carney said on ties with India

description: Canada will prioritize candidates with Canadian work experience to address labour shortages and enhance economic growth. The Express Entry system for 2025 introduces a new education category and removes the transport category, focusing more on high-priority sectors like healthcare, STEM, trades, and education.
title: Canada unveils big changes in Express Entry system
'Baap ka raaj hai kya': Tejashwi on BJP MLA asking Muslims to 'stay indoors' on Holi

description: Political parties have historically had a complicated relationship with CAG reports, intensifying around elections. The reports have been used both as ammunition by the opposition and concealed by ruling parties. Key examples include the 2G and coal block 'scams' which led to UPA's downfall.
title: CAG-itated politics: How audit reports upend political fortunes

description: Team India captain Rohit Sharma and ICC Chair Jay Shah celebrated India’s latest cricket triumphs, posing with the T20 World Cup and ICC Champions Trophy. India clinched the 2025 Champions Trophy title with a four-wicket win over New Zealand. This victory marks Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli's fourth ICC titles each, setting new records in Indian cricket history.
title: Watch: Rohit, Jay Shah display India's recent ICC trophies

description: Prince William is reportedly upset with Meghan Markle for allegedly channeling Princess Diana's style and using her memory to gain attention. This includes wardrobe choices reminiscent of Diana and the use of her legacy in personal and business projects, which has struck a nerve with William.
title: Prince William frustrated over Markle's 'attempt' to channel Princess Diana

description: Baba Vanga, known for her future predictions, has made notable prophecies for 2025. According to her, Aries, Gemini, Aquarius, Leo, and Taurus are set for a year of significant opportunities and success. Aries will see personal transformation, Geminis will experience substantial changes, Aquarians will implement ambitious goals, Leos will achieve financial success, and Taurus will find career stability.
title: Baba Vanga's predictions: 5 zodiac signs predicted to shine in 2025

description: A fashion show by Shivan & Narresh in Gulmarg during Ramzan has caused outrage in Jammu and Kashmir, with criticism over its timing and content. The designers apologized, acknowledging the hurt caused. Leaders like Mirwaiz Umar Farooq and Omar Abdullah condemned the event, and an inquiry was ordered to investigate the incident further.
title: 'Deeply regret': Designers apologise for Gulmarg fashion show

description: Air India has advised passengers to use lavatories appropriately after a Chicago-Delhi flight on March 5, 2025, was forced to return due to clogged toilets. The airline found inappropriate items like polythene bags, rags, and clothes had been flushed, causing significant discomfort and disruption to the passengers.
title: Flushed clothes, bags clog loos: Air India's appeal to flyers amid toilet row

description: Several small finance banks offer competitive fixed deposit rates, with some reaching up to 9%. Deposits are protected by DICGC insurance up to Rs 5 lakh, encouraging cautious investment within this limit.
title: Highest FD rates up to 9%: Which small finance banks are offering good FD rates?
'Kumbh water fit for bathing': Centre tells Parliament citing new CPCB report

description: Nate Vance, cousin of Vice President JD Vance, criticized the White House's treatment of Ukraine's President Zelenskyy, labeling it as an ambush. Nate, who volunteered to fight in Ukraine, expressed disappointment over JD's lack of effort to seek the truth about the war. "His own cousin was on the front lines. I could have told him the truth, without pretense, without personal interest. He never tried to find out more," Nate said.
title: 'Putin's useful idiots': Vance's cousin who fought for Ukraine slams VP
Sudiksha Konanki missing: Indian-origin student feared drowned in US

description: Former England captain Michael Vaughan praised India's deep bench strength, noting even a second-string team could reach the ICC Champions Trophy final. Led by Rohit Sharma, India won their third title, showcasing their cricketing depth and consistency. Vaughan's list included young stars like Yashasvi Jaiswal and experienced players such as Jasprit Bumrah.
title: Vaughan admits India's dominance, backs B-team to make CT final

description: Police arrested thirteen individuals after violent clashes in Mhow, Madhya Pradesh, where a rally celebrating India's ICC Champions Trophy victory faced stone pelting. The unrest caused injuries and vehicular damage. Law enforcement is investigating and monitoring the situation, ensuring stringent actions against those involved.
title: 13 held for violence in MP following celebratory rally of India's CT win
Gold smuggling case: Kannada actress Ranya Rao sent to judicial custody in Rs 12 cr

description: Axar Patel praised Rohit Sharma's leadership after India's nail-biting four-wicket win over New Zealand in the ICC Champions Trophy final. Rohit showcased his tactical skills and aggressive approach, leading India to their third title. Key contributions came from India's bowlers and a solid batting performance, cementing Rohit's legacy as a successful captain with two ICC trophies.
title: 'Haath mein trophy hai': Axar rates Rohit's captaincy after CT win

description: India triumphed over New Zealand in the Champions Trophy final, marking their second ICC title in nine months. Key decisions, including promoting Axar Patel in the batting order and backing KL Rahul over Rishabh Pant, played crucial roles, while Varun Chakravarthy's unexpected inclusion bolstered their spin attack. This win marked India's second ICC title in just nine months. They had previously clinched the 2024 T20 World Cup in June, defeating South Africa in the final in Barbados.
title: How India's strategic calls sealed the Champions Trophy title

description: Jonty Rhodes acknowledges Glenn Phillips as the best fielder of this generation after Phillips' exceptional performances in the ICC Champions Trophy 2025. Phillips amazed fans with stunning catches, including those of Virat Kohli and Shubman Gill. India won the final against New Zealand by four wickets, securing their third title.
title: 'Sorry Jonty, Phillips is the best fielder': Rhodes' response delights fans

description: US Secretary of State Marco Rubio and Elon Musk confronted Polish Foreign Minister Radoslaw Sikorski regarding claims about Starlink's reliability in Ukraine. Rubio dismissed Sikorski's concerns as baseless, while Musk emphasized Poland's minimal financial contribution and reaffirmed the unwavering support of Starlink for Ukraine.
title: Starlink fight for Ukraine: Angry Elon Musk to Polish FM, '...small man. You ...'
Who is Sudiksha Konanki? Young man questioned in Indian-origin student's mysterious disappearance

description: Tamil Nadu Chief Minister MK Stalin criticized Union Education Minister Dharmendra Pradhan for calling the Tamil Nadu government "dishonest" and "ruining" students' futures. Stalin reiterated his refusal to implement the National Education Policy, accusing Pradhan of arrogance and challenging the Centre's stance on educational funding.
title: 'Arrogant, need to be disciplined': TN CM Stalin hits out at Pradhan over NEP

description: The directorate general of health services (DGHS) has called on the IPL chairperson to regulate promotions for tobacco and alcohol during the upcoming IPL season starting 22nd March 2025.
title: DGHS writes to IPL chairperson to ban tobacco and alcohol ads

description: X (formerly Twitter), owned by Elon Musk, is facing a global outage impacting thousands of users. Reports on Downdetector show over 21,000 service disruption complaints in the US, with the outage affecting the app and website differently across regions. In India, the impact is less severe with around 1000 complaints. Users report app and website issues and login problems.
title: Elon Musk’s X down globally; here’s what users are saying

description: China is experiencing deflation, with consumer prices dropping by 0.7% and producer prices decreasing by 2.2%. The surplus industrial capacity and reduced consumer spending are contributing to this downturn. Analysts worry that without government intervention, deflationary pressures might persist, impacting business earnings and economic growth.
title: Four flash sales in a day! China hit by deflation - why economists are worried

description: Karnataka BJP president BY Vijayendra commented on the rare gold smuggling case involving actress Ranya Rao, arrested for smuggling 14.8 kilograms of gold. He indicated potential involvement of ministers and assured a deep CBI investigation. BJP leader Bharath Shetty highlighted attempts to involve Congress ministers, and the State Industrial Board clarified the land allotment to Rao's linked company.
title: Gold smuggling case: 'Ranya Rao tried to contact Congress ministers'

description: A fashion show during Ramzan in Gulmarg has led to political uproar, with BJP accusing J&K CM Omar Abdullah of involvement, which he denies. Mehbooba Mufti and religious leaders condemn the event as against Kashmiri values, prompting a promised government inquiry.
title: 'Hotel owned by relatives': BJP targets J&K CM over fashion show row

description: Mark Carney, set to become Canada's next Prime Minister, aims to strengthen trade relations with India. Winning 85.9% of the Liberal Party vote, Carney emphasizes diversifying trade ties and values-based commercial relationships. His expertise in India's economy through Brookfield Asset Management bodes well for enhancing Canada-India economic and strategic connections.
title: Mark Carney elected Canada's next PM: What he said about India

description: Several Congress leaders and workers were injured after the stage collapsed during a protest in Bhopal. Madhya Pradesh Congress in-charge Harish Choudhary emphasized the party's resilience amidst challenges. Congress MLAs, led by Umang Singhar, demanded an extension of the assembly budget session to address issues like unemployment, farmer struggles, and corruption, accusing the government of avoiding discussions.
title: Several Congress leaders injured after stage collapses during protest in Bhopal

description: Amazon's Jeff Bezos directed executives to buy out Barbara Broccoli's stake in the James Bond franchise after tensions escalated, spending nearly a billion dollars. Broccoli and Michael G. Wilson, who've controlled the franchise for 30 years, opposed Amazon's spinoff plans. Wilson's retirement spurred the sale, leaving the future of 007 uncertain under Amazon's new ownership.
title: What made Amazon founder say, I don't care what it costs, get rid of her …

description: Family members of a murder victim protested on the Akshardham-Ghaziabad road, demanding the arrest of the accused. Rohit, a 32-year-old man from Ghazipur village, was shot dead near Phool Mandi on National Highway-24. Police have detained two suspects and are actively investigating the case.
title: Man shot dead in Delhi; murder victim's family stages protest on road

description: India's triumph in the ICC Champions Trophy 2025 is being celebrated worldwide, with Google adding a special fireworks display for specific search keywords. Brands like Swiggy, Zomato, Uber, and Reliance Jio conveyed their congratulations through creative social media posts, praising the team's determination and spirit.
title: 10 Google searches for Champions Trophy 2025 to light up your screen

description: In two separate incidents early Monday, at least 4 labourers died and 13 were injured in a truck crash in Maharashtra's Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar, while a collision in Madhya Pradesh's Sidhi district killed 7 and injured 14. Both incidents involved speeding vehicles losing control.
title: 4 dead, 13 injured as truck overturns in Maharashtra's Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar

description: An Air India flight from Mumbai to New York was diverted back to Mumbai after a potential security threat was received mid-flight. The Boeing 777, carrying 303 passengers and 19 crew members, landed safely. The flight will be rescheduled, and passengers are provided with hotel accommodations and assistance. Air India emphasizes passenger and crew safety.
title: Air India's New York flight returns to Mumbai due to bomb threat

description: In March 2025, the Jaipur District Consumer Disputes Redressal Forum summoned Shah Rukh Khan, Ajay Devgn, and Tiger Shroff over allegations of misleading pan masala advertisements. The petition highlights the unrealistic claim of saffron content given the product's low price. Past endorsements and criticisms of celebrities like Ajay Devgn and Akshay Kumar over such brands were also discussed.

description: Elon Musk and Polish Foreign Minister Radoslaw Sikorski clashed online over the funding of Starlink, which is crucial for Ukraine's military. Musk asserted that the Ukrainian front would falter without Starlink, while Sikorski contended Poland pays $50 million annually for the service. US Secretary of State Marco Rubio defended Musk, emphasising Starlink's vital role in Ukraine's defense.
title: 'Be quiet, small man’: Musk's heated exchange with Polish minister

description: The Codava National Council has urged the central and Karnataka home ministers to ensure the safety of actress Rashmika Mandanna following intimidation by Congress MLA Ravi Kumar Gowda. The council condemned the MLA's actions and stressed that Rashmika has the right to personal choices without coercion.
title: 'Bullied by MLA': Codava Council seeks protection for Rashmika Mandanna

description: Luxury fashion brand Shivan & Narresh celebrated their 15th anniversary with a grand fashion show in Gulmarg, Jammu & Kashmir. However, the event faced backlash for its timing during Ramadan, leading to criticism from religious and political leaders for being culturally insensitive.
title: Called 'obscene' Shivan & Narresh’s skiwear showcase in Gulmarg sparks debate

description: Maharashtra's CM Devendra Fadnavis expressed support for removing Mughal king Aurangzeb's tomb but highlighted legal constraints due to its protected status by the Archaeological Survey of India. This issue emerged after BJP's Udayanraje Bhosale, a Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj descendent, advocated for its removal. The controversy was further fueled by Samajwadi Party MLA Abu Asim Azmi's praise of Aurangzeb.
title: ‘Cong put site under ASI’: Fadnavis on calls to remove Aurangzeb’s tomb

description: After India’s triumph in the ICC Champions Trophy 2025 final against New Zealand, head coach Gautam Gambhir, known for his serious demeanor, joined Navjot Singh Sidhu in a playful post-match shayari. Sidhu convinced Gambhir to do a bhangra move in celebration. This victory marked India's third Champions Trophy win. This was India's third Champions Trophy triumph, having previously won in 2002 (as joint winners with Sri Lanka) and in 2013.
title: Gautam Gambhir vs Navjot Sidhu in 'shayari' contest

description: India secured the Champions Trophy title with a four-wicket win over New Zealand, marking their 23rd victory in 24 matches at ICC events since 2023. Rohit Sharma's 76 and KL Rahul's unbeaten 34 guided India to 254-6 in 49 overs, chasing a target of 251. The win earned India $2.467 million in prize money.
title: How much prize money did India earn for Champions Trophy win?

description: Kia Norway humorously mocked Tesla amid global protests against Elon Musk's involvement with DOGE, by sharing an Instagram post featuring a sticker on its EV3 saying, “I bought this after Elon went crazy.” The protests arise from Musk's controversial actions and far-right support, causing Tesla owners to express their frustration while still loving the cars.

description: Elon Musk has experienced a significant $120 billion drop in net worth due to Tesla's declining share price and increased political scrutiny. Despite reduced consumer interest and emerging EV competition, Musk's previous resilience suggests he may overcome these financial setbacks. However, his political role raises questions about his commitment to Tesla's recovery.

description: Opposition leaders including Rahul Gandhi and TMC's Saugata Roy have called for a discussion on alleged voter list discrepancies, citing irregularities in states like Maharashtra, Haryana, and West Bengal. Accusations include fake entries and identical EPIC numbers. The Election Commission clarified that identical numbers are due to past manual mechanisms and do not indicate duplicate voters.
title: 'Question being raised': Rahul Gandhi demands discussion on voter's list

description: BJP mocks Congress after India's Champions Trophy victory, targeting Shama Mohamed for her past remarks about Rohit Sharma's fitness. The ruling party celebrates Sharma's achievements, highlighting recent wins under his captaincy, while urging respect for athletes and condemning political interference in sports.
title: 'Rats have gone into hiding': BJP's 'Pushpa' jibe at Congress after India's CT win

description: Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma celebrated India's Champions Trophy victory with a Dandiya dance. Skipper Rohit highlighted the team's strong mentality in overcoming external pressure and strategic use of spinners, leading to their success in the tournament despite criticism.
title: Representing India is not a joke: Rohit Sharma after Champions Trophy win

description: India's captain Rohit Sharma credited Shreyas Iyer as the 'silent hero' after India's ICC Champions Trophy win. Iyer played a crucial role throughout the tournament, particularly in the middle order. He ended as India's leading run-scorer and second overall, ensuring vital partnerships like the fourth-wicket stand with Axar Patel in the final against New Zealand.
title: Rohit Sharma reveals India's 'silent hero' in Champions Trophy triumph

description: Jammu and Kashmir CM Omar Abdullah called for a report on a controversial Gulmarg fashion show held during Ramzan, citing disregard for local sensitivities. The event faced backlash from religious leaders and activists, who labeled it obscene. Elle India removed related content from Instagram, and the show organizers apologized for any unintended discomfort.
title: 'Shock, anger understandable': J&K CM after fashion show in Gulmarg sparks row

description: Smallcap stocks have seen a remarkable recovery with a ₹4 lakh crore increase over four days. Despite significant gains, many stocks still trade well below their peak levels. Analysts urge caution, noting high valuations and the potential for further market corrections.
title: Smallcap stocks surge - but is this a bear market rally?

description: CRISIL's analysis shows that the cost for a vegetarian thali in February dropped by 1% year-on-year due to lower tomato and LPG prices. Meanwhile, non-vegetarian thali costs increased by 6% as broiler (chicken) prices surged.
title: Some relief! Cost of veg thali at home goes down in February

description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy humorously apologized days after facing criticism for his informal attire during his meeting with US President Donald Trump and vice president JD Vance. Zelenskyy has been wearing military-style attire during his country's ongoing war with Russia.
title: 'Sorry, I'm not in a suit': Zelenskyy's speech earns applause - watch

description: A Community Education Council meeting in Manhattan was disrupted by around 100 trans rights activists through silent dancing and heckling to oppose policies on transgender athletes. This ongoing protest has been led by trans teacher Alaina Daniels to challenge the council's review of gender identity sports policies, causing significant disruptions to other educational discussions.

description: The Indian cricket team will not hold an open-top bus parade after their Champions Trophy victory in Dubai, due to the upcoming IPL starting on March 22. Captain Rohit Sharma played a crucial role in India's four-wicket win over New Zealand. Pre-season camps for IPL franchises like Mumbai Indians and Sunrisers Hyderabad have already started.
title: Why no bus parade after India’s Champions Trophy triumph

description: Vanuatu Prime Minister Jotham Napat has ordered the cancellation of Lalit Modi's Vanuatu passport after discovering his intention to avoid extradition. This decision followed reports that Interpol had twice rejected India's request for an alert notice due to lack of judicial evidence, which would have automatically disqualified Modi's citizenship application.
title: 'Avoiding extradition': Vanuatu PM orders cancellation of Lalit Modi's passport

description: Vizianagaram Lok Sabha MP Kalisetti Appala Naidu will provide Rs 50,000 for every third child who is a girl in his constituency, deposited as a fixed deposit. This initiative aims to reach up to Rs 10 lakh by the time the girl is of marriageable age, encouraging population growth in Andhra Pradesh as per CM N Chandrababu Naidu’s vision.

description: The Enforcement Directorate raided locations connected to Chaitanya Baghel, son of former Chhattisgarh chief minister Bhupesh Baghel. The raids are part of an ongoing investigation into a liquor scam and money laundering case. The ED claims the scam caused a massive loss to the state exchequer, with a liquor syndicate allegedly siphoning off over Rs 2,100 crore.

description: Justin Trudeau, in an emotional speech as he steps down as Canadian Prime Minister, emphasized Canada facing critical economic challenges due to US tariffs. His successor, Mark Carney, accused Trump of undermining Canadian workers and vowed retaliation. The upcoming trade war and election period are set to define Canada's future direction under Carney's leadership.

description: An ambush on a Syrian security patrol near Latakia by pro-Assad gunmen has ignited days of clashes, leading to over 1,000 deaths and deepening sectarian tensions. The Alawite community, formerly central to Assad's regime, faces significant violence and persecution under the new Islamist-led government.

description: Mark Carney has been selected as Canada's next prime minister following Justin Trudeau's resignation. Carney criticized US President Donald Trump's trade policies and remarks about annexing Canada, vowing to defend Canadian workers and sovereignty. description: An Air India flight from Chicago to Delhi returned to Chicago after over ten hours due to technical issues, specifically non-functional toilets. Passenger accommodations were provided, and the airline offered full refunds and free rescheduling options.
title: Clogged toilets? Air India flight forced to return to Chicago after 10 hours in air

description: Federal immigration agents detained Mahmoud Khalil, a notable pro-Palestinian activist and Columbia University graduate, under Trump's executive orders. His arrest, claimed to be due to antisemitism, has sparked outrage from civil rights groups. His green card revocation is unusual, lacking criminal conviction.
title: Who is Mahmoud Khalil? Columbia University pro-Palestine activist detained by US

description: The celebration of India's 2025 Champions Trophy win in Dubai continued well into the night, with fans eagerly waiting outside the team hotel to see their heroes. Despite tight security, the players celebrated with their families, and memorable moments were shared among teammates and supporters. India won their third Champions Trophy on Sunday after beating New Zealand in the final.
title: White blazers and wild celebrations: Inside India’s Champions Trophy festivities

description: In Sambhal, police acted against a mosque and its imam for using a loudspeaker for 'azaan' at excessive volume, violating prescribed decibel limits. A case was registered, and the loudspeaker was seized. There have been multiple similar incidents recently, and authorities are enforcing noise pollution rules. Legal proceedings are ongoing.
title: Sambhal cleric booked, loudspeaker seized from mosque over 'azaan' volume

description: Ramchet, a cobbler from Sultanpur, Uttar Pradesh, is launching his brand 'Ramchet Mochi' with Rahul Gandhi's support, including a gifted machine and a meeting with prominent designer Sudheer Rajbhar. His business has significantly grown, moving from minor repairs to substantial monthly earnings and employing multiple artisans.
title: Backed by Rahul Gandhi, Sultanpur cobbler to launch 'Ramchet Mochi' brand

description: US President Donald Trump remains noncommittal about a potential recession in 2025. Despite reassurances from Trump and Commerce Secretary Howard Lutnick, economic indicators such as a negative GDP forecast and declining consumer confidence fuel concerns. Economists raise recession probabilities to 20%, amid market volatility and uncertainty over tariffs becoming permanent.
title: Will the US face a recession in 2025? President Trump responds

description: The PCB's absence from the podium at the ICC Champions Trophy final in Dubai has sparked criticism, particularly from former player Shoaib Akhtar. Despite hosting the tournament, Pakistan did not have any representatives present at the trophy presentation after India's victory over New Zealand.
title: Champions Trophy: Row over no PCB representation at final presentation
Watch: Saturday Night Live mocks Trump over Musk and Rubio’s clash

description: On December 6, students at Hameeri Kalan Senior Secondary School in Jhunjhunu, Rajasthan, celebrated as real-time technology from Digi Vritti enabled them to receive scholarships instantly. This pilot initiative by Piramal Foundation aims to transform the scholarship system, reducing delays and ensuring transparent disbursements, thereby helping deserving students access education funds swiftly.
title: A FasTag for scholarships? Jhunjhunu pilot shows way in easing student pain

description: A Rajasthan police constable was arrested for allegedly raping a pregnant woman in a hotel while her three-year-old son was present. The constable threatened to jail her husband, and following the assault, the woman approached police to file a complaint. The investigation is ongoing, and the constable has been suspended.
title: 'Threatened, slapped, gagged with towel': Cop rapes pregnant woman at Jaipur hotel

description: Communal clashes broke out in Mhow during celebrations after India's victory in the Championship Trophy, leading to arson and stone-pelting between two groups. Police intervened with lathicharge and teargas to control the situation. Several vehicles were set on fire, and heavy police deployment ensured the restoration of order.
title: Communal clashes in MP's Mhow during India’s Champions Trophy victory parade

description: Supreme Court has upheld the conviction of a tuition teacher for the 1984 sexual assault of a schoolgirl, affirming that a conviction can be based on the testimony of the victim, even without injuries to the private parts. The court dismissed the teacher’s allegations about the victim's mother, emphasizing the independence of the rape case from her character.
title: 40 years after rape, SC says injury to private parts not must for conviction

description: Orissa High Court has acquitted Madan Kanhar, a 42-year-old man previously convicted of murder, due to insufficient evidence. The court found discrepancies in the testimonies and an absence of conclusive forensic findings, leading to a judgment in favor of Kanhar after he had spent 14 years in jail.
title: After 14 years in jail, murder convict acquitted as HC cites ‘lack of evidence’

description: The budget session of Parliament resumes with several controversies simmering, including Trump's tariff comments, duplicate voter ID cards, and the three-language policy. Parliament will discuss the ongoing violence in Manipur and the Waqf amendment bill, with the government seeking approval for President’s rule in Manipur. The state’s budget is also up for discussion.
title: Finance minister to table Manipur budget today, Shah to seek Prez rule nod

description: Indian drug companies are set to revolutionize diabetes treatment with affordable generic versions of Empagliflozin, following the expiry of its patent. Estimated to significantly cut costs and improve access for over 10 crore diabetics, Mankind Pharma and others will offer the drug at a fraction of its original cost, easing financial burdens and enhancing heart and kidney health.
title: Key diabetes drug to cost up to 90% less in a few days

description: The Ethics and Medical Registration Board rejected a patient's appeal in February 2023, despite the National Medical Commission agreeing to consider such appeals in September 2022. The EMRB's decision was questioned since the board is vacant. The rejection appears to be a copy of a previous denial from 2022, raising concerns about the decision-making process.
title: NMC overrules SC’s and its own decision, rejects patient’s appeal

description: Amid the US-China tariff war, Indian solar industry stakeholders urge the government for safeguard duty on Chinese imports of polysilicon, ingot, and wafers. They highlight the need for incentives to boost domestic manufacturing, ensuring investment protection against Chinese dumping, which threatens India's solar goals. Moreover, fiscal incentives and policy reorientation are requested to enhance upstream segment growth.
title: Solar ingot, wafer units seek duty safeguard against Chinese dumping

description: An indefinite shutdown has been called in tribal-dominated areas of Manipur by the Kuki-Zo Council, supported by the ITLF. The protest is against the resumption of civilian traffic between the hills and the valley, following clashes with security forces that resulted in one Kuki protester's death and over 20 injuries.
title: Uneasy calm in Manipur as tribal areas shut down over protester’s death

description: MNS chief Raj Thackeray criticizes the central government for its failure to clean the Ganga river while highlighting potential health hazards of using Kumbh water. Thackeray emphasized the need for religious faith to be guided by logic rather than superstition, attracting criticism from BJP and Shiv Sena leaders.
title: Why did Raj Thackeray refuse to drink water brought from Kumbh?

description: The Baptist Church of Mizoram (BCM) aims to encourage a higher birth rate among its members, foreseeing benefits for both the state and the church. Additionally, they plan to address social issues such as drug addiction, HIV/AIDS, and corruption through local church committees.
title: Mizoram church urges its members to have more babies, save faith
